This guide is to help you to try out different Processor Topologies on your machine.
Your choice has to be based on the memory available and the number of cores per node.

The topologies given is actually used for each grid (Yin, Yang) and so the
total number of cores used is given in MPICORES.

NOTE that this is a mini-test so, it is designed to run with a minimum of 2 MPIcores.
The maximum MPICORES that can be used is 64. More cores can be used if using OpenMP.

TOPO: NPEX x NPEY  MPICORES TOTAL   Gridpoints on each Tile
TOPO:    1 x    1  MPICORES=     2  SUBDOMAINS=  127 x   56 
TOPO:    1 x    2  MPICORES=     4  SUBDOMAINS=  127 x   28 
